<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-09-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="626" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                        <head>No. 626.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hunter</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Heap</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-09-22"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 22,
                                    1880</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 273.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your cipher telegram, dated at
                            Constantinople the 17thinstant, has been received. It reads as follows,
                            viz: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Legal counsel necessary prosecution of murderers. Do you
                                    authorize it?</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Upon the 20th instant the Department replied thereto as follows, viz:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>You are authorized to employ counsel.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>These telegrams are understood to relate to the case of Dr. Parsons and
                            servant recently murdered near Ismid, in Turkey.</p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>W. HUNTER,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting
                                Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>